# validation-rules

Core Validation Components:

1. Mental Health Program Structure Validation
- Enforces required fields specific to mental health services:
  - Program name, organization, level of care categorization
  - Service delivery method (in-person, virtual, hybrid)
  - Age range validation with special "and up" handling
  - Geographic service area boundaries

2. Crisis Content Validation
- Special handling for crisis resource categorization
- Verification requirements for crisis service providers
- Contact method validation for crisis programs
- Response time commitment verification
- 24/7 availability confirmation

3. Neutrality Enforcement
- Detection of marketing language
- Validation of objective program descriptions
- Removal of subjective quality claims
- Standardized terminology enforcement
- Clinical language compliance checks

4. Service Area Validation
- Geographic boundary verification
- Multi-region service area validation
- County-level coverage confirmation
- Virtual service delivery validation
- Hybrid program location requirements

5. Verification Requirements
- 90-day reverification enforcement
- Multiple verification source validation
- Source credibility assessment
- Data freshness tracking
- Program status monitoring

6. Healthcare Privacy Compliance
- PHI exclusion validation
- Contact information verification rules
- Location data precision requirements
- Accessibility information validation

7. Program Categorization Rules
- Level of care validation (PHP, IOP, Outpatient)
- Service domain classification
- Age range overlap detection
- Insurance coverage validation
- Specialty service verification

Implementation Files:
- js/data-validator.js: Primary validation implementation
- js/program-detail.js: Program-specific rules
- js/modules/search.js: Search-related validations

